      "text": "The two papers \"Calibrating Noise to Sensitivity in Private Data Analysis\" by Dwork, McSherry, Nissim and Smith are the same paper, but the 2016 version is published in the Journal of Privacy and Confidentiality, whereas the 2006 version was published in the proceedings of the Third Theory of Cryptography Conference (TCC). The main difference between these two versions is the publication format and the publisher. The 2016 version is a journal paper and it's published by Journal of Privacy and Confidentiality and the 2006 version is a conference paper and it's published by Springer. The content of both versions should be the same, and the 2016 version is an updated version of the 2006 version."
